Jenna Etheridge, News24ER24 (Picture: Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A man was shot and killed in Northriding, north of Johannesburg, Gauteng paramedics said on Saturday.A local security company called paramedics to Epsom Road on Friday night and found a man lying still in the middle of the road, said ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring.He had a gunshot wound to the chest and leg.He showed no signs of life and was declared dead on the scene.Police were investigating. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.